  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your<strong> potatoes </strong>(skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, your<strong> dried oregano </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp – these are your<strong> oregano fries</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
